    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models/gemini-2.5-flash:generateContent?key=YOU-API-KEY",
        "sendBody": true,
        "specifyBody": "=json",
        "bodyParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            {}
          ]
        },
        "jsonBody": "={{\n{\n  \"contents\": [\n    {\n      \"parts\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": `You are generating a highly professional and tailored job application email.\nThe email must be written STRICTLY FROM the candidate (Jayesh Borse) TO the recruiter, hiring manager, or company representative.\n\n========================\nCANDIDATE PROFILE\n========================\nName: Jayesh Borse\nEducation: Integrated MCA (Master of Computer Applications)\nLinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/in/jayesh-borse-67408b325\n\nCore Skills:\n- Java\n- Advanced Java\n- JavaScript\n\nBackend:\n- Spring Boot\n- Spring Security\n- Hibernate / JPA\n- REST APIs\n\nFrontend:\n- React.js\n- HTML5\n- CSS3\n\nDatabases:\n- PostgreSQL\n- MySQL\n\nTools:\n- Git\n- GitHub\n- Postman\n\nConcepts:\n- OOP\n- MVC Architecture\n- Exception Handling\n- Microservices Fundamentals\n- Data Structures & Algorithms\n\nALL AVAILABLE PROJECTS:\n1. AI Job Hunter Automation Platform (Built with n8n, PostgreSQL, Gemini AI)\n2. Smart Mobility Platform (Full-stack logistics/tracking solution)\n3. Java Console Job Portal (Pure Java & OOP application)\n\n========================\nJOB DETAILS\n========================\nJob Title: ${$json.job_title}\nCompany Name: ${$json.company_name}\nJob Description: ${$json.job_description}\n\n========================\nEMAIL GENERATION RULES\n========================\n1. Write completely from Jayesh Borse's perspective. Do not simulate a hiring platform or recruiter.\n2. Maximum 250 words. Use a professional, concise, and confident tone.\n3. PHRASING IMPROVEMENTS:\n   - Do NOT write \"My Integrated MCA education and practical experience align well...\". Instead, use: \"As an Integrated MCA graduate with hands-on experience in Java backend development...\".\n   - Group the tech stack elements naturally: \"I possess strong proficiency in Java, Spring Boot, REST API development, and MySQL, which align closely with the technical requirements of this role.\"\n4. PROJECT SELECTION RULE: Select the single most relevant project based on the job description and mention ONLY that project. Do not mention the others. Use this exact mapping:\n   * Java Developer roles → Mention only: Java Console Job Portal\n   * Backend Developer roles → Mention only: AI Job Hunter Automation Platform\n   * Full Stack Developer roles → Mention only: Smart Mobility Platform\n   * Frontend Developer roles → Mention only: Smart Mobility Platform\n5. Do NOT use these phrases:\n    * \"I came across your profile\"\n    * \"I would like to discuss an opportunity with you\"\n    * Placeholders like [Your Name] or [Company Name]\n6. If the job is NOT related to Software Engineering, Java Development, Backend Development, Frontend Development, Full Stack Development, or Web Development, return EXACTLY:\n{\n  \"subject\": \"NOT_RELEVANT\",\n  \"email\": \"NOT_RELEVANT\"\n}\n7. Subject format: Application for [Job Title] – Jayesh Borse\n8. CLOSING CTA: End with appreciation for consideration and a confident, personalized call to action exactly like: \"I would welcome the opportunity to discuss how my skills and project experience can contribute to ${$json.company_name}'s engineering team.\" Follow this directly with the LinkedIn profile link.\n\n========================\nOUTPUT FORMAT (CRITICAL)\n========================\n- Return raw, clean JSON matching the structure below.\n- Do NOT wrap the response in markdown.\n- Do NOT use \\`\\`\\`json or \\`\\`\\` code blocks anywhere in your response.\n- Start directly with the opening curly brace { and end with the closing curly brace }.\n\n{\n  \"subject\": \"...\",\n  \"email\": \"...\"\n}`\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n}}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.4,
